Dear Mr. Raut,

 

Please stop insisting on us taking an AMC contract for the units supplied by
your company which are fitted on our trucks.


We have not selected this because we do still believe that your units will
not give much problem and will continue to give us smooth service.

 

Every other  mail from your company these days  seems to be only to push us
to taking an AMC. Business has become very difficult and we are trying to
minimize cost on all fronts. Taking an AMC for 24-30 units would cost us Rs.
60-80,000. We do believe that our cost on call-out attention to the units
will be much less than that.

 

If the units become so unreliable that we will need regular service, we
would be constrained to escalate our concern to Castrol and in an extreme
situation, consider other vendors for reasons of service and reliability.

 

I do hope I am clear.

 

Thanks & regards

Byram R. Dhalla

Director

B. D. Dhalla Transport Pvt. Ltd.

